Comment:
The agentive participle is homonymous with the action nominalization except for three-syllable stems, but even then, the agentive participle is identical with the short variant of the action nominalization used in compounds:
čállin 1) write + agentive participle (’written by’)  or 2) action nominalization ’(act of) writing’);
jorgalan translate-AG.PTCP >< jorgaleapmi translate-AN, but jorgalan- in, e.g., jorgal-an-bargu translate-AN-work
